> Looking for a super quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Szechuan Chicken Breast Stir-Fry in just 15 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Boil the @Jasmine Rice{150%g}, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and cover.

Once hot, fry the @diced British chicken breast{260%g}, @sliced mushrooms{80%g} and @mangetout{80%g}, ~{5-6%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Meanwhile, cut the @lime{1} into wedges.

Next, add the @Szechuan paste{3/4%sachet}, @soy sauce{15%ml}, @ketjap manis{25%g}, @honey{1%tbsp} and @water{2%tbsp}. Bring to the boil and stir. Lower the heat, then simmer, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Taste and season. Add a splash of water if needed.

Divide the rice and stir-fry between #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the @roasted white sesame seeds{5%g}.

Serve with the lime wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!